Theorem “Identity of ≢”: (p ≢ false) ≡ p
Proof:
    (p ≢ false) ≡ p
  =⟨ “Symmetry of ≢”⟩
    (false ≢ p) ≡ p
  =⟨ (3.14) ⟩
    (¬ false ≡ p) ≡ p
  =⟨ “Negation of `false`” ⟩
    true ≡ p ≡ p
  =⟨ “Identity of ≡”⟩
    true




    

