Theorem (3.39) “Identity of ∧”: p ∧ true ≡ p
Proof:
    p ∧ true   
  =⟨ “Golden rule”⟩
    p ≡ (true ≡ p ∨ true)
  =⟨ “Zero of ∨”⟩
    p ≡ (true ≡ true)
  =⟨ “Identity of ≡”⟩
    p

