Theorem (3.42) “Contradiction”: p ∧ ¬ p ≡ false
Proof:
    p ∧ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Golden rule” ⟩
    p ≡ (¬ p ≡ (p ∨ ¬ p))
  =⟨ “LEM”⟩
    p ≡ (¬ p ≡ true)
  =⟨ “Commutativity of ¬ with ≡” ⟩
    p ≡ ¬ (p ≡ true)
  =⟨ “Associativity of ≡” ⟩
    p ≡ ¬ (true ≡ p)
  =⟨ “Commutativity of ¬ with ≡”⟩
    p ≡ (¬ true ≡ p)
  =⟨ “Associativity of ≡”⟩
    p ≡ (p ≡ ¬ true)
  =⟨ “Definition of `false`”⟩
    p ≡ (p ≡ false)
  =⟨ “Definition of ≡”⟩
    false

