Theorem (3.48): p ∧ q ≡ p ∧ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
Proof:
    p ∧ q ≡ p ∧ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Golden rule” ⟩
    p ≡ q ≡ (p ∨ q) ≡ p ≡ ¬ q ≡ (p ∨ ¬ q) ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Associativity of ≡” ⟩
    ((p ∨ q) ≡ (p ∨ ¬ q)) ≡ p ≡ q ≡ p ≡ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Distributivity of ∨ over ≡”⟩
    (p ∨ (¬ q ≡ q)) ≡ p ≡ q ≡ p ≡ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Commutativity of ¬ with ≡”⟩
    (p ∨ ¬ (q ≡ q)) ≡ p ≡ q ≡ p ≡ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Identity of ≡” ⟩
    (p ∨ ¬ true) ≡ p ≡ q ≡ p ≡ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Definition of `false`”⟩
    (p ∨ false) ≡ p ≡ q ≡ p ≡ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Identity of ∨”⟩
    p ≡ p ≡ q ≡ p ≡ ¬ q ≡ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Identity of ≡”⟩
    (¬ p ≡ p) ≡ (¬ q ≡ q)
  =⟨ “Commutativity of ¬ with ≡”⟩
    ¬ (p ≡ p) ≡ ¬ (q ≡ q)
  =⟨ “Identity of ≡”⟩
    ¬ true ≡ ¬ true
  =⟨ “Definition of `false`”⟩
    false ≡ false
  =⟨ “Identity of ≡”⟩ 
    true

