Theorem (3.66) “Strong modus ponens”:
    p ∧ (p ⇒ q) ≡ p ∧ q
Proof:
    p ∧ (p ⇒ q)
  =⟨ “Material implication”⟩
    p ∧ (¬ p ∨ q)
  =⟨ “Distributivity of ∧ over ∨”⟩
    (p ∧ ¬ p) ∨ (p ∧ q)
  =⟨ “Contradiction”⟩
    (false) ∨ (p ∧ q)
  =⟨ “Identity of ∨”⟩
    p ∧ q

